                            <h1>R7-2019-18: Multiple Hickory Smart Lock Vulnerabilities</h1>
                            <div>
                                <ul class="blog-post-info">
                                        <li class="date">Aug 01, 2019</li>
                                                                            <li class="time">9 min read</li>
                                    <li class="name">
                                        <a href="/blog/author/tod-beardsley/">Tod Beardsley</a>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                                <ul class="blog-post-social float-right">
                                    <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&amp;url=https://www.rapid7.com/blog/post/2019/08/01/r7-2019-18-multiple-hickory-smart-lock-vulnerabilities/&amp;title=R7-2019-18%3a+Multiple+Hickory+Smart+Lock+Vulnerabilities&amp;summary=The+Hickory+Smart+BlueTooth+Enabled+Deadbolt+IoT+ecosystem+(which+includes+mobile+applications+as+well+as+a+cloud-hosted+web+and+MQTT+infrastructure)+has+several+vulnerabilities." class="linkedin" onclick="window.open(this.href, 'linkedin-share', 'width=520,height=570');return false;"></a></li>
                                    <li><a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=R7-2019-18%3a+Multiple+Hickory+Smart+Lock+Vulnerabilities&amp;url=https%3a%2f%2fwww.rapid7.com%2fblog%2fpost%2f2019%2f08%2f01%2fr7-2019-18-multiple-hickory-smart-lock-vulnerabilities%2f" class="twitter" onclick="window.open(this.href, 'twitter-share', 'width=550,height=235');return false;"></a></li>
